The devel list is intended for developers to discuss issues with package
development, not general user problems. In future please use
support.bioconductor.org for this sort of question.

That said, the errors come early on in your output:

Configuration failed because libcurl was not found. Try installing:
 * deb: libcurl4-openssl-dev (Debian, Ubuntu, etc)
 * rpm: libcurl-devel (Fedora, CentOS, RHEL)
 * csw: libcurl_dev (Solaris)

Configuration failed because openssl was not found. Try installing:
 * deb: libssl-dev (Debian, Ubuntu, etc)
 * rpm: openssl-devel (Fedora, CentOS, RHEL)
 * csw: libssl_dev (Solaris)

So you either need to ask your sysadmin to install libcurl4-openssl-dev and
libssl-dev, or do it yourself using

sudo apt get install libcurl4-openssl-dev libssl-dev


